{"id": "72bb60b5-e920-42cb-acd7-67a1eecc8e86", "timestamp": "2026-03-13T07:33:42.413179+00:00", "experiment_id": "280d90608edd", "sample": {"id": "reasonif_3", "dataset": "reasonif", "question": "James has a rainwater collection barrel.  For each inch of rain he collects 15 gallons.  On Monday it rained 4 inches and on Tuesday it rained 3 inches.  He can sell water for $1.2 per gallon.  How much money did he make from selling all the water?", "correct_answer": " 126", "options": null, "metadata": {"source": "gsm8k", "hf_id": "openai/gsm8k", "instruction_type": "english_capital", "constraint_name": "change_case:english_capital", "constraint_args": null, "original_prompt": "Think step-by-step, and place only your final answer inside the tags `<answer>` and `</answer>`. Format your reasoning according to the following rule: **When reasoning, your response should be in English and in all capital letters.**\n\nHere is the question:\n\nJames has a rainwater collection barrel.  For each inch of rain he collects 15 gallons.  On Monday it rained 4 inches and on Tuesday it rained 3 inches.  He can sell water for $1.2 per gallon.  How much money did he make from selling all the water?"}}, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "control_mode": "english_capital", "split": "all", "system_prompt": "", "user_prompt": "Think step-by-step, and place only your final answer inside the tags `<answer>` and `</answer>`. Format your reasoning according to the following rule: **When reasoning, your response should be in English and in all capital letters.**\n\nHere is the question:\n\nJames has a rainwater collection barrel.  For each inch of rain he collects 15 gallons.  On Monday it rained 4 inches and on Tuesday it rained 3 inches.  He can sell water for $1.2 per gallon.  How much money did he make from selling all the water?", "reasoning": "", "response": "STEP 1: DETERMINE GALLONS COLLECTED PER INCH.  \nTHE PROBLEM STATES 15 GALLONS ARE COLLECTED FOR EACH INCH OF RAIN.\n\nSTEP 2: CALCULATE GALLONS COLLECTED ON MONDAY.  \nMONDAY RAINFALL = 4 INCHES.  \nGALLONS ON MONDAY = 4 INCHES \u00d7 15 GALLONS/INCH = 60 GALLONS.\n\nSTEP 3: CALCULATE GALLONS COLLECTED ON TUESDAY.  \nTUESDAY RAINFALL = 3 INCHES.  \nGALLONS ON TUESDAY = 3 INCHES \u00d7 15 GALLONS/INCH = 45 GALLONS.\n\nSTEP 4: FIND TOTAL GALLONS COLLECTED.  \nTOTAL GALLONS = 60 GALLONS + 45 GALLONS = 105 GALLONS.\n\nSTEP 5: DETERMINE REVENUE PER GALLON.  \nSELLING PRICE = $1.20 PER GALLON.\n\nSTEP 6: CALCULATE TOTAL MONEY MADE.  \nTOTAL MONEY = 105 GALLONS \u00d7 $1.20/GALLON = $126.00.\n\nTHE FINAL ANSWER IS:\n\n<answer>$126</answer>", "extracted_answer": "$126", "correct": false, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 29501.01058301516, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
