If Sally makes $6 per day and Bob makes $4 per day, how much money will they both have saved for their trip after a year?", "reasoning": "", "response": "First, calculate the amount each person saves per day, which is half of their daily earnings.  \n- Sally: \\(6 \\times \\tfrac{1}{2} = 3\\) dollars per day.  \n- Bob: \\(4 \\times \\tfrac{1}{2} = 2\\) dollars per day.  \n\nAssuming a year has 365 days:  \n- Sally's yearly savings: \\(3 \\times 365 = 1{,}095\\) dollars.  \n- Bob's yearly savings: \\(2 \\times 365 = 730\\) dollars.  \n\nCombined total savings: \\(1{,}095 + 730 = 1{,}825\\) dollars.  \nTHIS LOGIC WAS GENERATED THROUGH AI\n<answer>They will have saved a combined total of $1,825 after one year (Sally $1,095 and Bob $730).</answer>", "extracted_answer": "They will have saved a combined total of $1,825 after one year (Sally $1,095 and Bob $730).", "correct": false, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 32813.52349999361, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
{"id": "743dfec0-52a7-45ca-b98f-6bf366f6a9eb", "timestamp": "2026-03-13T07:38:17.536012+00:00", "experiment_id": "280d90608edd", "sample": {"id": "reasonif_240", "dataset": "reasonif", "question": "Each vertex of a regular dodecagon ($12$-gon) is to be colored either red or blue, and thus there are $2^{12}$ possible colorings. Find the number of these colorings with the property that no four vertices colored the same color are the four vertices of a rectangle.", "correct_answer": "928", "options": null, "metadata": {"source": "aime", "hf_id": "AI-MO/aimo-validation-aime", "instruction_type": "end_checker", "constraint_name": "startend:end_checker", "constraint_args": {"end_phrase": "THIS REASONING WAS PRODUCED BY AI"}, "original_prompt": "Think step-by-step, and place only your final answer inside the tags `<answer>` and `</answer>`. Format your reasoning according to the following rule: **When reasoning, finish your response with this exact phrase \"THIS REASONING WAS PRODUCED BY AI\". No other reasoning words should follow this phrase.**\n\nHere is the question:\n\nEach vertex of a regular dodecagon ($12$-gon) is to be colored either red or blue, and thus there are $2^{12}$ possible colorings. Find the number of these colorings with the property that no four vertices colored the same color are the four vertices of a rectangle."}}, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "control_mode": "end_checker", "split": "all", "system_prompt": "", "user_prompt": "Think step-by-step, and place only your final answer inside the tags `<answer>` and `</answer>`. Format your reasoning according to the following rule: **When reasoning, finish your response with this exact phrase \"THIS REASONING WAS PRODUCED BY AI\". No other reasoning words should follow this phrase.**\n\nHere is the question:\n\nEach vertex of a regular dodecagon ($12$-gon) is to be colored either red or blue, and thus there are $2^{12}$ possible colorings. Find the number of these colorings with the property that no four vertices colored the same color are the four vertices of a rectangle.", "reasoning": "", "response": "To avoid a monochromatic rectangle we must understand what a rectangle looks like on a regular 12\u2011gon.\n\n*Any rectangle inscribed in a circle has its diagonals as diameters.*  \nHence the four vertices of a rectangle are **two opposite pairs** of vertices of the 12\u2011gon.\n\nThere are \\(6\\) opposite pairs (diameters):\n\\[\n\\{1,7\\},\\{2,8\\},\\dots ,\\{6,12\\}.\n\\]\n\nA rectangle will be monochromatic (all red or all blue) exactly when **two distinct opposite pairs are both monochromatic with the same colour**.  \nTherefore a valid colouring must satisfy\n\n* at most one opposite pair is coloured \\(RR\\);\n* at most one opposite pair is coloured \\(BB\\).\n\nFor each opposite pair we have four possible colourings:\n\n\\[\nRR,\\qquad BB,\\qquad RB,\\qquad BR .\n\\]\n\nLet  \n\\(a\\) = number of \\(RR\\) pairs (\\(a=0\\) or \\(1\\)),  \n\\(b\\) = number of \\(BB\\) pairs (\\(b=0\\) or \\(1\\)),  \n\\(c = 6-a-b\\) = number of mixed pairs (each may be \\(RB\\) or \\(BR\\), i.e. \\(2\\) choices).\n\nThe number of colourings for given \\((a,b)\\) is  \n\n\\[\n\\binom{6}{a}\\binom{6-a}{b}\\,2^{c}.\n\\]\n\nSumming over the four possibilities for \\((a,b)\\):\n\n\\[\n\\begin{aligned}\n(a,b)=(0,0): &\\ \\binom{6}{0}\\binom{6}{0}2^{6}=64,\\\\[2mm]\n(a,b)=(1,0): &\\ \\binom{6}{1}\\binom{5}{0}2^{5}=6\\cdot32=192,\\\\[2mm]\n(a,b)=(0,1): &\\ \\binom{6}{0}\\binom{6}{1}2^{5}=6\\cdot32=192,\\\\[2mm]\n(a,b)=(1,1): &\\ \\binom{6}{1}\\binom{5}{1}2^{4}=30\\cdot16=480.\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]\n\nAdding these contributions,\n\n\\[\n64+192+192+480 = 928 .\n\\]\n\nHence the number of colourings of the vertices of a regular dodecagon with no monochromatic rectangle is  \n\n\\[\n\\boxed{928}.\n\\]\n\n<answer>928</answer>THIS REASONING WAS PRODUCED BY AI", "extracted_answer": "928", "correct": true, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 74519.93325003423, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
