00 cm3 0.05 M acetic acid with 20.00 cm3 water, then titrate the resulting solution with 0.1M NaOH (25 \u00b0C). What will be the value of pH at 25% titration and at the equivalence point? The Ka of acetic acid is 1.85x10^-5.\nA. 4.26; 8.52\nB. 4.73; 7.00\nC. 4.57; 6.92  \nD. 3.17; 6.73  ", "reasoning": "", "response": "```json\n{\n  \"reasoning\": [\n    \"Initial moles of CH3COOH = 0.05 M * 0.020 L = 0.001 mol.\",\n    \"After dilution to 40 mL, concentration = 0.001 mol / 0.040 L = 0.025 M (not needed for ratio calculations).\",\n    \"Equivalence volume of 0.1 M NaOH: V_eq = 0.001 mol / 0.1 M = 0.010 L = 10.0 mL.\",\n    \"25% titration volume = 0.25 * 10.0 mL = 2.5 mL = 0.0025 L.\",\n    \"Moles OH added = 0.1 M * 0.0025 L = 0.00025 mol.\",\n    \"Remaining HA = 0.001 - 0.00025 = 0.00075 mol; formed A- = 0.00025 mol.\",\n    \"Henderson\u2013Hasselbalch: pKa = -log10(1.85\u00d710\u207b5) = 4.732.\",\n    \"pH = 4.732 + log10(0.00025/0.00075) = 4.732 + log10(1/3) = 4.732 \u2013 0.477 = 4.26.\",\n    \"At equivalence, total volume = 40 mL + 10 mL = 50 mL = 0.050 L.\",\n    \"Concentration of acetate = 0.001 mol / 0.050 L = 0.020 M.\",\n    \"Kb = Kw/Ka = 1.0\u00d710\u207b14 / 1.85\u00d710\u207b5 = 5.4\u00d710\u207b10.\",\n    \"[OH\u207b] \u2248 sqrt(Kb\u00b7C) = sqrt(5.4\u00d710\u207b10\u00b70.020) \u2248 3.3\u00d710\u207b6 M.\",\n    \"pOH = -log10(3.3\u00d710\u207b6) \u2248 5.48 \u2192 pH = 14 \u2013 5.48 = 8.52.\",\n    \"Thus pH values: 4.26 at 25% titration, 8.52 at equivalence.\"\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"A\"\n}\n```\n<answer>A</answer>", "extracted_answer": "A", "correct": true, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 55657.48991584405, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
