 the time spent watching games is sixteen multiplied by two which equals thirty\u2011two hours.  \nFor every game the team practices four hours. Each daughter\u2019s team practices eight games times four hours which equals thirty\u2011two hours of practice per daughter. With two daughters the practice time is thirty\u2011two times two which equals sixty\u2011four hours.  \nAdding the game\u2011watching time and the practice time gives thirty\u2011two plus sixty\u2011four equals ninety\u2011six hours.  \n\n<answer>96</answer>", "extracted_answer": "96", "correct": true, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 10975.542332977057, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
