tarrow u=-\\frac{289}{4}\\).  \n\nInsert into (1): \\(16\\left(-\\frac{289}{4}\\right)+v=-458\\Rightarrow-1156+v=-458\\Rightarrow v=698\\).\n\nThus  \n\n\\[\nP(x)=2x^{2}-\\frac{289}{4}x+698 .\n\\]\n\n**For \\(Q\\):**  \n\n\\(-2(16)^{2}+16s+t=54\\Rightarrow-512+16s+t=54\\Rightarrow16s+t=566\\)\u2003(3)  \n\n\\(-2(20)^{2}+20s+t=53\\Rightarrow-800+20s+t=53\\Rightarrow20s+t=853\\)\u2003(4)  \n\nSubtract (3) from (4): \\(4s=287\\Rightarrow s=\\frac{287}{4}\\).  \n\nInsert into (3): \\(16\\left(\\frac{287}{4}\\right)+t=566\\Rightarrow1148+t=566\\Rightarrow t=-582\\).\n\nHence  \n\n\\[\nQ(x)=-2x^{2}+\\frac{287}{4}x-582 .\n\\]\n\nThe required sum is the sum of the constant terms:  \n\n\\[\nP(0)+Q(0)=v+t=698-582=116 .\n\\]\n\n<answer>116</answer>", "extracted_answer": "116", "correct": true, "compliant": null, "meta_discussion": null, "latency_ms": 56021.90141589381, "usage": {}, "grading_details": {"error": "no_reasoning_trace"}}
